node.text:
You don’t know what the future holds, but you can know the kind of character that you’re marrying. 
These are the 3 things I look for in a relationship and what I’m looking for in a husband.. I encourage you to write yours down and don’t compromise or settle❤️

node.title: For all my singles out there

node.text: Comparison will kill your contentment and distract you from your purpose. There is power in choosing to be secure in who you are. You’re not enough on your own, but with God you have all you need!

Who am I? 
How can I be confident? 
How can I empower others to walk in confidence? 

Join @demitebow and me in 2 DAYS!! (on Wed, February 3rd at 8:00 EST) for a live interactive workshop where we will talk about our journeys in finding true confidence and some practical steps that helped us along the way. You weren’t made to struggle alone, we’re better together! 
Link is in my bio to sign up 💕

node.text:
I am so honored to be a part of @auburnmbb AUTLIVE program. 
I’ve had the privilege of helping my dad with Auburn youth basketball camps for the last four years. One of my favorite campers, Sam Cunningham, was diagnosed at the age of 12 with acute lymphoblastic leukemia. Over the last 3 years, Sam has had many doses of chemotherapy, 13 surgical procedures, and has spent hundreds of days in the hospital.  Sam is currently in the maintenance phase of his treatment. His “end of treatment” date is listed as July 3rd 2020. I stand with Sam in his fight. He was one of my campers and he is a friend for life. ❤️
Join Coach Bruce Pearl and me in support of #AUTLIVE. Buy your T-shirt today: link in bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Madison Prewett on August 18, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, ocean, twilight, nature, coast and sky.

node.text:
My challenge to you today: don’t try harder, trust more. 

Maybe you have felt time and time again “I’ve tried..” I’ve tried to live right. I’ve tried to fight for what I believe. I’ve tried to find godly relationships. I’ve tried to follow Jesus. I’ve tried. And you’re exhausted. You’re tired of trying. Because you’re tired of failure. You’re tired of being let down. In these moments we begin to lose the hope that God can truly set us free and that blessing could actually await us. 
But the cold hard truth is: you can’t do it on your own. No matter how hard you try. 

Today I challenge you. Stop trying, even on your best days- your strength alone isn’t enough. But with God, even on your worst of days, you have everything you need. Even when it’s hard: trust. Even when it’s lonely: trust. Even when it doesn’t make sense: trust. Even when it doesn’t look the way you thought it would: trust. 

You have a choice to make. You can try and control. Or you can choose to trust. You can’t have both. This week has been a tough week for me personally. There’s also so much going on around the world it feels overwhelming sometimes. I know I can’t do it on my own. But I choose to trust. I hope you will too. 

Tag someone who needs to hear this. 🤍

node.text:
⚡ GIVEAWAY TIME ⚡

My fav haircare company @evahairnyc just launched their Brass to Sass Brunette Collection: a bright blue, brunette-toning shampoo and conditioner that reduces orange and brassy tones for rich, radiant brunette hair. I’ve been using it and my hair has never looked better (even after the first wash!). Brunettes - if you haven’t tried it yet, you MUST. I'm obsessed! 😍

To celebrate their new game changing collection, @evahairnyc and I have partnered up to give you all a chance to win $2,000 worth of @evahairnyc + @apple goodies! 
 
WINNER WILL RECEIVE:
💕 $500 Eva NYC gift card
💕 iPhone 12 Pro Max
💕 AirPods Pro

🏅 PLUS we're giving TEN runners-up $50 @evahairnyc gift cards 🏅

HOW TO ENTER:
1️⃣ FOLLOW @evahairnyc + me, @madiprew 
2️⃣ LIKE this post 
3️⃣ TAG 3 of your besties in a comment below
➕ BONUS ENTRY: Share this post to your stories and tag @evahairnyc 

Winner will be selected and announced on 8/19/2022 via DM. Must be at least 18 years or older to enter. Giveaway open worldwide. Good luck everyone! 

#evanyc #giveaway #internationalgiveaway #contest
